There are days I'm confident about my art, then there are days where I feel inferior and get insecure (a lot). 

I try to turn the latter into my motivation to do better, to push my limits. Sometimes it's exhausting, but the good thing is art is a lifelong journey =] ♡

Like, it's not my goal to be a full-time artist. I like art on the side. I don't aim working for any art industry. I just like drawing people's OC, meeting artists, having a loving community. I don't really have an end goal. I just like the journey. *cue dramatic music*

I want to say I just draw for fun.

But given that I sometimes earn $ from my art, technically, I'm a "professional" artist? Idk. I don't like labels much when it comes to this because there's so much pressure in being a "professional" that I can't be myself.
Least favorite thing to draw is hands...but I am trying. I promise.
